    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Marsh</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 58.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-11-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 10, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 20th of October (No.
                            53) has been submitted to the President, and he authorizes me to
                            communicate to you his thanks for the clear exposition it gives of
                            Italian politics in the present interesting crisis.</p>
                <p>It is easy to see that European interests and passions are beginning to
                            engage some of that attention which during the last year European
                            statesmen have so unprofitably for both continents bestowed upon the
                            unhappy affairs of the American people.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George P. Marsh</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
